Hi Lev,

there has been some progress concerning our calculations: the scans with the Br tip are finished. (You can check if you want.) It seems there is a lot less contrast with a Br tip, but we have to check that using a good van-der-Waals force. I have found a better description of my tip after correction of some errors, but I'm still trying to find an even better one.

For testing, I have added some long-range force to the short range force-distance curves. It looks like the order of magnitude corresponds well to the experiment, but to give a more quanitative desription, I need a better experimental van-der-Waals curve. The only value for a Hamaker constant that I found was from the Israelachvili for CaF_2. I hope Alexis knows where else to look for one. Or maybe you have a better value for KBr-KBr and KBr-Si and so on?

Cheers

Regina

