Hi Lev,

there is no derivation. From the force, I get the frequency shift using the integral over F*cos(wt) (the inverse Duerig method or whatever you want). As I was lazy, I did not multiply with f_0/(2c_L) to get the frequency shift, so my small programm gives me c_eff then which is proportional to the frequency shift. I devided the experimental curves by this factor, f_0/(2c_L). So I compare ceff to ceff. max and min in the experiment means the black and the white spots - the minima and the maxima of the observed contrast.

Do you have more questions or did I explain it well? Maybe we should talk on the phone if it becomes more complicated?

Regina

