Dear Dr. Kantorovich,

Thank you for your E-mail on July 29.
Regarding your ticket, I talked to the person in charge. They said it is
customary to use business class for any person to be invited from foreign
countries. That's why yen 550,000 is allocated for airplane ticket. It is
government rule to make the actual expense closest possible to the estimated
amount. In other words, it is necessary for you to find a ticket very close
to Yen 550,000.  You are not allowed to use extra money saved by finding
cheaper ticket to other things than buying tickets.  We also think it is
very strange Japanese government rule. But we have to follow it. Please
understand.

So, please look for a ticket in business class.
Thank you for your cooperation.

