Okay, I'm aware these things often annoy, but this is the best puzzle
I've heard in a long time.  Prizes include the undying respect and
admiration of your peers.

A burgler breaks into a monastery, and paints green (unbeknownst to
them), the noses of some (at least one) of the monks.  The monks are
forbidden from ANY form of communication, and only see each other once a
day.  When the monks gather on day one, the abbot instructs them that
any monk who realises he has a green nose must leave IMMEDIATELY.  There
is no other communication.  This message is delivered at every daily
congregation, after which the monks return to their cells.  After the
meeting on the seventh day, all of the monks with green noses leave
immediately, simultaneously and (as said before) without communication.

How many monks had green nose? Why?

Anwers on a postcard please.

