Dear Colin,


>Colin Wilkin wrote:
>
>Dear Colleagues,
>
>I know that many of you are away - but I have also seen many of you
>around College in the last couple of days. In order to get a fairly
>representative sample of opinion, I would appreciate a reply to the
>following question which I circulated last week.
>
>===================================================================
>
>Our current scheme for the award of honours was devised with the
>introduction of the MSci degree almost a decade ago. An important   
>element of the scheme is the initial discounting of the worst half  
>unit from a student's performance each year. It has been clear for  
>some time that some students, particularly the weak but also some   
>middle-ranking ones, are deliberately throwing a course. This was
>not our intention when we introduced the scheme.
>
>Following discussions with the Visiting Examiners, who are aware of
>the problem, I would like to float the idea of half-weighting the
>TWO lowest marks in a given year rather than zero-weighting the
>lowest. By construction, this methodology must lower the year 
>average slightly. I would estimate this effect to be about 1.0-1.5%.
>[One cannot simply estimate it by looking at current results because
>some students are currently ditching one course per year.]
>

I agree with your proposed change in the method of calculating the average
mark for a student in each programme year to be used with the existing
weightings for the degree. However I suspect that you have over estimated
the magnitude of the average reduction in the yearly marks.


>I am therefore writing to ask for your opinion in the matter so that
>I can decide whether to try to get approval for the scheme. If the
>scheme were modified, it would only affect incoming students. It
>might be possible to get it in position for the September entry,
>though this would require insertions into the student handbook.
>

I would prefer that the new scheme applied to ALL years from September
2001. This would ensure a common scheme for all students, not just the
first-year ones. This will be less confusing for the students, especially
the first-year ones, who are more likely to believe the second-year ones
who tell them that we ignore completely the lowest module mark (on a
1/2-unit basis) rather than what we hope they have read in the student
handbook. (It would not be applied retropectively to re-sitting students.)
Nevertheless the details of the new algorithm must be prominantly
displayed in the student handbook issued in September to all students, not
just new ones. 


>I would be very grateful if you could let me have your opinion on
>the matter.
>
>Kindest regards,
>
>Colin


Best wishes,
Dave

