Dear Colleagues,

Retirement of Professor R.L. Souhami

As you will probably know, Professor Souhami is retiring from his post as
Dean of the Faculty of Clinical Sciences and Principal of the Royal Free &
University College Medical School, and his last day here will be the 18th
September.  Prof. Souhami was a medical student at the UCH Medical School
and has continued to work at UCH (now UCLH) and the Medical School
throughout most of his career.   He is therefore very well known to staff
in all parts of those organisations and wider UCL.   His contribution to
Oncology has been considerable, as clinician, researcher, teacher and
'facilitator', both locally and internationally.   More recently he has
achieved a great deal as the first Director of Research and Development at
UCLH, and then as Principal of the Medical School.   His insight, kindness,
wit and wisdom will be greatly missed by colleagues and medical students
alike.   We have been very fortunate to have had him guiding the Medical
School through a time of considerable change in the last five years.

I believe many of his colleagues will wish to mark their recognition and
appreciation of his contribution in both clinical and academic fields.   A
message book is available for signing at the Reception Desk, Medical School
Administration, Drayton House, 30 Gordon Street (from 9.30 am - 4.30 pm).
Alternatively you may find it easier to provide a message on a label and
post it back to the address below.

Any contributions towards a gift for Prof. Souhami should be sent to the
address below by Friday 31st August, or hand delivered to Mrs. Sylvia Brady
at the Medical School Reception Desk.   Cheques should be made payable to
University College London.

