1. RESEARCH PHYSICISTS AND ENGINEERS

   TeraView Ltd, Cambridge (Commercial)
   
   TeraView Ltd. is an innovative start-up company in the Cambridge area
   which is currently recruiting highly motivated research physicists and
   engineers to work on the development and commercialisation of
   Terahertz (THz=1012Hz) technology, which has applications to medical
   and non-medical diagnostic imaging as well as wireless communications.
   The Company, which will work closely with the University of Cambridge,
   major laboratories throughout Europe and with international companies,
   will develop semiconductor sources and detectors of THz radiation
   based on a variety of novel phenomena. Very promising results are now
   leading to clinical trials of the Company's technology as well as
   applications in other non-medical areas. Further posts have become
   available and the company is seeking to fill the following positions:
   
   Semiconductor Processing Physicist / Engineer
   
   This position entails the fabrication of novel THz emission and
   detection structures using conventional techniques of silicon and
   compound semiconductor processing.
   
   At least 3 years' post-graduate experience in clean room processing
   techniques is desirable. The person will have a degree in physics,
   material science, electrical or semiconductor process engineering.
   
   You must be able to work effectively in a team, having a careful and
   methodical approach to problem solving and be able to propose and
   instigate your own solutions.
   
   The applicant will work part-time at Cavendish Laboratory, University
   of Cambridge and will report to the Directors at TeraView Limited.
   
   Semiconductor Device Physicist
   
   This position will entail the design of devices that emit and detect
   broad-band THz radiation from the far-infrared to the mid-infrared for
   use in a spectroscopic imaging system. Techniques will include the use
   of quantum wells and superlattices as well as novel photoconductive
   semiconductor structures.
   
   Relevant post-doctoral experience in semiconductor devices emitting
   and detecting THz radiation up to mid-infrared is desirable.
   
   A Ph.D. in semiconductor physics is essential. Experience in using
   ultrashort pulse laser (sub 20 fs) is desirable, but not essential.
   You will be working in as part of a multi-disciplinary team.
   
   Applications Engineer / Semiconductor Device Physicist
   
   The role of this applicant will be developing new CW THz emitting and
   detecting devices. Sources and detectors of THz radiation based on a
   variety of novel phenomena including near-infrared/visible pumping
   techniques, quantum cascade structures, and other novel approaches
   will be investigated, including various aspects of emitter design,
   fabrication, and emission measurements. Applications of the technology
   to wireless communications and imaging will be investigated.
   
   The applicant should have 3-years post-graduate experience in the
   applications of frequencies in the microwave range or frequency-mixing
   techniques with lasers together with a first or upper second honours
   degree in physics or electrical engineering.
   
   You must be able to work effectively in a team or alone, having the
   abilities to solve the wide range of complex problems in this region
   of the spectrum.
   
   An excellent package of benefits including share options will be
   available for the successful candidates.
   
