KEELE UNIVERSITY

DEPARTMENT OF COMPUTER SCIENCE AND
SCHOOL OF EARTH SCIENCES AND GEOGRAPHY

RESEARCH ASSISTANT POST IN GEOGRAPHICAL INFORMATION SYSTEMS;
SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL OBJECT DATABASES


The Department of Computer Science is seeking to appoint a=20
Research Assistant to work within the Geoinformatics Research=20
Group on an existing EPSRC Research Project: Spatial and Temporal=20
Object Databases.  The appointment is for 18 months fixed term=20
with effect from the earliest possible start date.

The project is a collaboration between Keele University and the=20
University of Manchester, with support from the Ordnance Survey=20
of Great Britain. The aim of the project is the development of a=20
spatio-temporal information system.

The Research Assistant will work in the Geoinformatics Research=20
Group in the Department of Computer Science, in collaboration=20
with the School of Earth Sciences and Geography.  The Department=20
of Computer Science has substantial research interests in GIS and=20
software engineering, and the Geoinformatics Research Group has=20
an international reputation in spatial data modelling,=20
spatio-temporal information systems and multiresolution spatial=20
data models.  The aim of the Group is to produce research that is=20
theoretically well founded, but links to applications. The Group=20
has links to many national and international centres of research=20
excellence in the field.  The Research Assistant will have the=20
opportunity to take advantage of this global network of contacts.

Candidates should have, or be about to complete, a Ph.D. in a=20
relevant area such as GIS, Geography, Information Systems or=20
Computer Science.

The focus of this post is the development of applications that=20
test the spatio-temporal information system during its=20
development.  Applications under current investigation include=20
land-use changes and uses of longitudinal data sets, but the=20
Research Assistant will have opportunities to develop new=20
applications based on his/her interests.

Starting salary will be on Point 6 of the Research Grade 1A,=20
=A319.486 per annum (current rate).  Informal enquiries may be=20
directed to Chris Johnson (tel: 01782 584090=20
c.johnson@cs.keele.ac.uk) or Keith Mason (tel: 01782 583170,=20
k.t.mason@esci.keele.ac.uk).

Application forms are available from the Personnel Department,=20
Keele University, Keele, Staffordshire ST5 5BG or Fax your=20
request to 01782 583471 or Email: vacancies@keele.ac.uk.  Please=20
quote Ref: RE01/23.

Closing date 30th July, 2001.  The Department expects to hold=20
interviews during the week beginning 13th August, 2001.

AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER


