Dear CSAR Users, 
 This bulletin for July 2001 includes the following topics: 

 - CSAR TECHNOLOGY REFRESH 
     - Green upgrade to 512 processor 

 - SOFTWARE/SYSTEM UPDATE 
     - Fourier Upgrade 
     - -cpr option for checkpointing 
     - Amber 6.0 - SMP version 
     - Gromacs 2.0    
     - Dl_Poly

 - NEW EDITION OF CSAR FOCUS

 - TRAINING COURSES FOR 1ST SEMESTER 2001/2002 

 - WORKSHOPS/SEMINARS 
     - Euro-Par 2001  (Early Registration now open)
     - EUROGRAPHICS 2001 (REGISTRATION NOW OPEN)
     - GGF-2 (July 15-18 2001)
     - VECPAR'2002 (June 26-28) 

******************************************************************** 

CSAR TECHNOLOGY REFRESH 

Green upgrade to 512 processors 
=============================== 

The next 256 processors for Green arrived last Thursday and the 
installation process has started. In order to integrate into a 
single 512 processor system it will be necessary to close down the 
Green service for about 2 days - this is likely to be within the 
next two weeks. The system will initially be configured to run jobs 
of up to 256 processors, but this will be increased towards the full 
size of the machine. Please let us know if you have an early requirement 
to run such large jobs. 

As mentioned previously, Green is binary compatible with Fermat, so 
programs should be developed on Fermat and then submitted to Green. 
The faster interconnect on Green should result in improved performance 
of parallel codes. With 512 GBytes memory, Green will have more than 
double the total memory of Turing and 4 times the memory per processor. 

In order to access Green, your consortium/project must have Green 
resources - your PI can trade for Green cpu in the normal manner. 
Individuals can self register - you will need access username and 
password from your PI. 

More information about the service on Green are provided via the CSAR 
web pages: 
http://www.csar.cfs.ac.uk/green/ 

The Code Portability Assessment Programme, announced in recent CSAR 
Bulletins is also available to assist in porting codes to Green - 
please see: http://www.csar.cfs.ac.uk/using/portability.shtml 

If you need additional information please contact the CSAR helpdesk 
(csar-advice@cfs.ac.uk). 

********************************************************************** 

SOFTWARE/SYSTEM UPDATE 

Fourier Upgrade 
=============== 
  
Following on from the upgrade of the inter-processor network to 
Myrinet 2000 last month, the head-node of Fourier (the CSAR 32 
processor Intel Itanium cluster) has been upgraded from a Pentium 
to a dual processor Itanium node. Users are now recommended to 
compile and debug their codes on the head node for speed. As a 
side effect, many users passwords have had to be reset. Please 
contact csar-advice@cfs.ac.uk if you find that you can no longer 
log in. The batch queues will be restored shortly. 

Usage remains free of charge to registered CSAR users. For further 
information see www.csar.cfs.ac.uk/fourier. 
  

-cpr option for checkpointing 
============================= 

On both Fermat and Green, you are strongly encouraged to include 
the -cpr option when executing a program in batch via the mpirun 
command. This allows the checkpoint or restart of MPI jobs that 
consist of a single executable file running on a single system. 
If you do not specify this option, it may not be possible to 
successfully checkpoint the job. 
  
Amber 6.0 - SMP version 
======================== 

The Amber 6.0 suite has now been installed on Fermat 
and Green for shared memory to complement the parts 
of the suite that have been parallelised with MPI. 
Details on how to use the package are on our web 
pages:

http://www.csar.cfs.ac.uk/software/amber.shtml


Gromacs 2.0
===========

The Molecular Dynamics chemistry code, Gromacs, has 
now been installed on Fermat and Green. Details on 
how to use this software are available on our web 
pages:

http://www.csar.cfs.ac.uk/software/gromacs.shtml


Dl_Poly
=======

DL_POLY (a classical MD chemistry code from Daresbury) 
has now been installed on Green and Fermat. For further 
information see:

http://www.csar.cfs.ac.uk/test/software/dl_poly.shtml
 
*********************************************************************

NEW EDITION OF CSAR FOCUS
==========================

The summer 2001 edition of CSAR Focus is now available at:

http://www.csar.cfs.ac.uk/general/newslett/csarfocus_summer01.pdf

********************************************************************* 
TRAINING COURSES FOR 1ST SEMESTER 2001/2002

Forthcoming courses in next semester
====================================

Please note that the course timetable for the next semester is now
available at:

http://www.csar.cfs.ac.uk/using/courses/


******************************************************************** 
WORKSHOPS/SEMINARS 

GGF-2 (July 15-18 2001)
=======================
2nd International Global Grid Forum Meeting, is being held 
in Vienna, Virginia USA from July 15 - 18, 2001. For further 
details see:  
        
http://www.gridforum.org/Meetings/GGF2/


Euro-Par 2001  (28th - 31st August)
==============
Early Registration dead line is 27th July. Contact csar helpdesk 
(0161  275 6824) for a copy of advanced programme. For registration 
and further information see Euro-Par 2001 website:
http://europar.man.ac.uk/
  

EUROGRAPHICS 2001 (4-7 September)
=================
Advanced Programme now available, for further information 
please see EUROGRAPHICS 2001 website: 
http://www.man.ac.uk/MVC/EG2001/

        
VECPAR'2002 (June 26-28)
========================
5th International Meeting on High Performance Computing for
Computational Science. For further information please see:
http://www.fe.up.pt/vecpar2002/ 

